nib.text:
Police detained a suspect after a man was killed during an assault near Field in South Minneapolis Thursday night, officials said. 

At around 9:30 p.m., police responded to a report of an assault in the 4700 block of Elliot Avenue S. 

Upon arrival, family members directed police into the home where a son was reportedly attacking his father. 

According to a report from [KARE11](https://www.kare11.com/article/news/crime/minneapolis-domestic-assault-murder-charge/89-41573e14-2986-4acc-83fb-9df877d16e69) police entered the home and discovered the father had been killed. 

The son was taken into custody pending charges. 

Homicide detectives are investigating.
